\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 48. F. capillifolia} Dufour in Roemer & Schultes,{\i  Syst. Veg.}{\b  2}: 735 (1817) ({\i F. scaberrima} Lange, non Steudel). Densely caespitose; stems 35-60 cm; non-flowering shoots intravaginal. Leaves plicate, very slender, strongly scabrid, slightly pungent; veins 5-7, with a sclerenchyma-strand below but not touching each vein and at the margins; ribs 1-3(-5), not very prominent; epidermal cells large; sheaths closed for ½-¾ of their length, not decaying into fibres, with infolded margin of 1 row of cells; ligule minutely auriculate. Panicle 6-10 cm, the branches shortly hairy. Spikelets 7·5-9 mm. Upper glume 5·1-5·8 × 1·3-1·6 mm, narrowly lanceolate, long-acuminate. Lemma 5·2-6·2 × 1·7-2 mm, lanceolate, long-acuminate. Anthers c. ½ as long as palea. Ovary glabrous. {\i Woods and scrub; calcicole. S. & S.E. Spain. }Hs.
