\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. F. tatrae} (Csakó) Degen,{\i  Magyar Bot. Lapok}{\b  3}: 171 (1904) ({\i F. amethystina} var.{\i  tatrae} Csakó). Densely caespitose; stems up to 45 cm; non-flowering shoots intravaginal. Leaves 0·7-0·9(-1·3) mm wide, plicate; veins (5-)9-11(-13) with 7-9 sclerenchyma-strands, some touching the veins from below; ribs (5-)7-11, prominent; sheaths closed for 1/2-2/3 of their length, with infolded margin of 1 row of cells; ligule minutely auriculate, densely ciliate. Panicle c. 10 cm, the branches sparsely hairy. Spikelets 7·9-8·6 mm. Upper glume 3-3·4 × 1·4-1·6 mm, ovate-lanceolate, shortly acuminate. Lemma 4·2-4·6 × 2·3-2·4 mm, ovate-lanceolate, shortly acuminate. Anthers more than ½ as long as palea. Ovary glabrous or subglabrous. 2n = 14. {\i Mountain grassland; calcicole. • W. Carpathians.} Cz Po.
