\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 53. F. borderi} (Hackel) K. Richter, {\i Pl. Eur.}{\b  1}: 97 (1890). Densely caespitose; stems 10-30 cm; non-flowering shoots intravaginal. Leaves (0·5-)0·6-0·85 mm wide, plicate, pungent, often curved; veins 5-7, with a sclerenchyma-strand below each vein, that of mid-vein and margin touching the vein; ribs 5, very prominent, occasionally with sclerenchyma; sheaths closed for 2/3 of their length, scarcely fibrous, with infolded margin of 2 rows of cells; ligule short, ciliate. Panicle c. 5 cm, dense, the branches glabrous. Spikelets 7-7·6 mm. Upper glume 4·3-4·9 × 1·3-1·6 mm, ovate-lanceolate, shortly acuminate. Lemma 5·2-5·8 × 1·6-2 mm, acuminate. Anthers less than ½ as long as palea. Ovary glabrous or subglabrous. 2n = 14.{\i  Siliceous rocks, }2300-2700{\i  m. • Pyrenees.} Ga Hs.
